page.title: 03HIGH WYCH
page.content: During the past five or so years, the village of High Wych has been recognisably changed, by increasing traffic and building.High Wych has had two major developments in the past five years, Rivers has been sold off and has been turned into a garden centre and Dixons garage has been turned into fourteen houses. High Wych used to be part of the old parish of Sawbridgeworth.The church dates from 1860,it has a parish magazine called The Link.There is a High Wych school attended by 175 children.There is a fair bit of history in High Wych despite the new houses.The amount of people in High Wych has increased in the last 8 or 9 years.There is only one shop in High Wych called High Wych General Stores and they get their supplies from the firm Londir and from Cash and Carry.
